at|mitche: bidding: When S bid 2NT, Jacoby, North's responses are as follows: 
a) a bid of a new suit at the 3 level shows a singleton, or possibly a void.
b) a new suit at the 4 level shows a minimum 5-5 hand with concentrated strength in the 2 suits
c) a jump to 4 of your major shows a minimum hand with no shortness
d) a bid of 3 of your major shows a good hand, 
and e) a bid of 3N shows a really good hand
d) and e) are slam try bids... 
