Example: 1@c  X  1@S  ???
Now, your double (in Standard bidding) is not responsive. It is a penalty double! You are showing 4+ spades AND about 9 points
Here is the logic: pard has 13 points (about) and for his double of 1@C, at least 3 spades.Right?
You have 4 card "support" for spades and with 8 or 9 points, you have the balance of strength, too
So you have the majority of the spades and the majority of the points. Think the opponents are going to like being in spades?|
