moviemaker: And as a reminder:

A general guideline for responding when your partner's opening bid is doubled by RHO:

1@d   X   XX = 10+ (balanced with lack of support, forcing)
1@d   X   1NT = 8-10 (and don't do it if you don't want to play in NT)
1@d   X   2NT = 11-12
1@d   X   1y = 4+card, forcing (only if you don't mind to be raised)
1@d   X   2@c (2 over 1: strong 5-card, less than 10 pts, NF)
1@d   X   2@h (jump shift: 6-card, no outside defense, 4-6 pts to the Ace)

1@d   X   2NT "Flip-Flop" = pre-empt
1@d   X   3@d = limit raise
=> Partner can still play the 3NT

1@h/@s   X   2NT = Jordan, limit raise or better, 4+ support (some play 3+)

This concludes this presentation. Hope you enjoyed, Karen10|
